  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to add syncing time ETA in Beacon Node API response. That value is present in the logs, but it would be nice to make it visible in the API. This is related to https://github.com/ethereum/beacon-APIs/issues/166 .\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nLighthouse/v1.5.1-b0ac346/x86_64-linux\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nThe `/eth/v1/node/syncing` API does not expose syncing time ETA in the response.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nA field exposing syncing time ETA is present in the `/eth/v1/node/syncing` API endpoint response when the beacon node is syncing.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nA new field is added in the `/eth/v1/node/syncing` API endpoint to include syncing time ETA when the beacon node is syncing.\r\n",
